WEBVTT

00:20.354 --> 00:25.316
Your weight is 113.9 pounds.

00:32.241 --> 00:33.908
You gonna make me hurt you?

00:34.535 --> 00:35.868
- No
- I didn't think so.

01:11.655 --> 01:14.365
Are you alright? Did I hurt you?

01:17.995 --> 01:19.203
Bob!

01:20.122 --> 01:22.957
Bob! What's wrong?
What happened? Talk to me.

01:24.793 --> 01:27.211
Oh, my God! OK, honey,
hang on, hang on.

01:28.589 --> 01:30.047
911, what is your emergency?

01:30.174 --> 01:33.926
Yes, we need an ambulance
at 10600 Xavier, unit 4-B.

01:34.052 --> 01:36.262
My husband can't breathe.

01:36.388 --> 01:40.266
Oh, my God, he's turning blue.
You have to send someone now, please!

01:40.392 --> 01:41.517
Hurry!

02:50.254 --> 02:52.421
You blow-dry your hair?

02:52.548 --> 02:54.549
Oh, sorry. Did I wake you up?

02:54.675 --> 02:56.384
You blow-dry your hair?

02:57.719 --> 03:00.012
Excuse me for actually caring
what I look like.

03:00.138 --> 03:02.807
I think the word you're looking for
is "obsessing."

03:03.809 --> 03:05.351
You've been at it for almost an hour.

03:05.477 --> 03:07.895
If you wanted in,
all you had to do was say so.

03:08.021 --> 03:10.106
I don't want in. I want sleep!

03:10.232 --> 03:13.276
It's about time you got up anyway.
It's almost 9:00.

03:15.279 --> 03:17.488
This isn't gonna work.

03:18.824 --> 03:21.325
- What?
- You staying here.

03:21.451 --> 03:24.829
You're kicking me out? After one night?

03:25.664 --> 03:28.499
Why, you think we should
try counseling first?

03:30.252 --> 03:32.336
Why do you want to sleep
on a couch anyway?

03:32.462 --> 03:35.756
You got money. At least
until the divorce is finalized.

03:38.510 --> 03:42.388
I'll be out of your hair tomorrow.
What's left of it.

03:56.570 --> 03:57.904
It was three days ago.

03:58.030 --> 04:00.364
My throat got really dry
and then my tongue

04:00.490 --> 04:02.575
felt like it was blowing up
like a balloon.

04:02.701 --> 04:04.785
I assume somebody
checked for food allergies.

04:04.912 --> 04:07.580
- The first two doctors both did.
- Next one said it was a panic attack.

04:07.706 --> 04:09.832
The one after that wanted
to take his tonsils out.

04:09.958 --> 04:12.627
The last one had no idea,
just referred us to Dr. House.

04:12.753 --> 04:14.045
It says the attack was preceded

04:14.171 --> 04:16.672
by some sort of
strenuous physical activity.

04:17.341 --> 04:19.008
- Yeah.
- What were you doing?

04:25.557 --> 04:26.933
Awesome.

04:27.059 --> 04:29.769
A sex fiend with a swollen tongue.

04:29.895 --> 04:32.688
Just think of all the places
I can make Foreman search.

04:32.814 --> 04:36.317
He's not a sex fiend.
He's a happily married man.

04:36.443 --> 04:37.693
No such thing.

04:42.157 --> 04:43.991
What are you doing?

04:46.954 --> 04:48.788
Testing a new caffeine delivery system.

04:48.914 --> 04:51.082
He didn't get his beauty sleep.

04:51.208 --> 04:54.919
Wilson's moved in and apparently
has unusually loud toenails.

04:55.045 --> 04:56.629
If they're into rape fantasies,

04:56.755 --> 04:58.506
S&M is on the menu as well.

04:58.632 --> 05:01.842
Neck trauma could cause vocal cord
paroxysms, which could cause choking.

05:01.969 --> 05:04.845
I didn't see any sign of
trauma, and they were remarkably open.

05:04.972 --> 05:06.180
I asked about STDs

05:06.306 --> 05:09.392
and they admitted participating
in a threesome a few months ago.

05:09.518 --> 05:12.269
A hundred bucks says they're
as miserable as the next couple.

05:12.396 --> 05:14.188
Another guy, or girl?

05:14.314 --> 05:16.732
Girl. His wife's college roommate.

05:18.443 --> 05:20.903
If he's not happily married,
I don't know who could be.

05:21.029 --> 05:24.407
They're looking for something. If you're
happy, you've got nothing to look for.

05:24.533 --> 05:26.450
His wife arranged it
for an anniversary present.

05:26.576 --> 05:29.161
If you ask me, if two people
really trust each other,

05:29.287 --> 05:32.790
a threesome once every seven years
might actually help a marriage.

05:34.584 --> 05:38.170
OK, I say we stop the DDX
and discuss that comment.

05:39.297 --> 05:40.548
I'll take the bet.

05:42.342 --> 05:45.553
Maybe the first doctor was right.
Food allergy explains the anaphylaxis.

05:45.679 --> 05:46.846
Could be neurological.

05:46.972 --> 05:49.682
Progressive bulbar paralysis
would explain the symptoms.

05:49.808 --> 05:52.685
No. ALS would affect his facial muscles
before his throat.

05:52.811 --> 05:54.729
What if the problem's not in his throat?

05:54.855 --> 05:58.232
That would be a little odd considering
that's where all his symptoms are.

05:58.358 --> 06:00.026
- Says who?
- The patient.

06:00.152 --> 06:03.863
And since most patients can't tell
their ulna from their anus,

06:03.989 --> 06:06.282
I'm guessing this guy also doesn't know
the difference

06:06.408 --> 06:08.117
between choking and suffocating.

06:08.243 --> 06:10.786
His throat might be fine,
his lungs might be messed up.

06:10.912 --> 06:14.290
Get more blood, a chest CT
and a body plethysmograph.

06:14.416 --> 06:16.751
Unless, of course, you think
we should be asking the patient

06:16.877 --> 06:18.044
where his anus is first.

06:20.380 --> 06:23.549
It feels like I have to urinate
and then when I try to go...

06:24.634 --> 06:26.594
Pull up your pants.

06:27.471 --> 06:30.681
- It's my prostate, isn't it?
- Nope, not your prostate.

06:31.808 --> 06:34.185
- Herpes.
- Herpes?

06:34.853 --> 06:36.937
Herpes. Your turn.

06:37.898 --> 06:40.733
If it makes you feel any better, half
the patients who come into this place

06:40.859 --> 06:44.028
- have some sort of crotch rot.
- No, it doesn't.

06:44.154 --> 06:47.656
Look, this is impossible.
I've been married for 20 years.

06:47.783 --> 06:49.283
Have you had any sex in those 20 years?

06:49.409 --> 06:52.369
- Yes, of course.
- Then that's how you got it.

06:52.496 --> 06:55.164
The only person I've had sex with
is my wife.

06:56.291 --> 06:57.583
Bummer.

06:58.168 --> 07:01.504
Take this once a day.
Tell your wife to do the same.

07:01.630 --> 07:02.880
It's not going to cure it,

07:03.006 --> 07:05.591
but it will lessen the frequency
of the outbreaks.

07:05.717 --> 07:07.051
But there must be some mistake.

07:07.177 --> 07:08.552
You got any kids?

07:08.678 --> 07:11.055
- Yeah.
- Any of them take guitar lessons?

07:11.932 --> 07:13.974
- No.
- Tennis? Art? Acting?

07:14.101 --> 07:16.560
My daughter does karate. Why?

07:17.229 --> 07:19.063
Give this to her sensei.

07:19.689 --> 07:23.400
- Oh, wait. Does your wife play tennis?
- No.

07:23.527 --> 07:26.654
That's what I figured.
Never hurts to make sure.

07:27.572 --> 07:29.198
For Miyagi.

07:32.410 --> 07:34.286
I'm gonna close the shutter now.

07:34.412 --> 07:37.248
I need you to pant, kind of like a dog.

07:39.543 --> 07:41.544
That's good. Keep going.

07:43.463 --> 07:46.298
Can I ask you a personal question?

07:47.509 --> 07:49.885
Uh, I guess.

07:50.011 --> 07:54.473
The threesome and the role-playing.

07:54.599 --> 07:56.934
Is that because things get boring?

07:59.020 --> 08:00.229
No.

08:00.730 --> 08:04.775
We just enjoy our fantasies.

08:08.113 --> 08:10.114
- Are you married?
- No.

08:13.201 --> 08:16.162
You can go back to taking
the deep breaths now.

08:17.330 --> 08:20.583
Marriages don't fail
because couples get bored.

08:21.168 --> 08:23.878
They fail because while they're dating,

08:24.004 --> 08:25.379
people pretend to be the person

08:25.505 --> 08:27.673
they think their partner wants,
and then...

08:27.799 --> 08:30.885
Well, there's only so long
you can keep that up.

08:32.304 --> 08:35.222
Maybe they are that person while
they're dating, but then they change.

08:35.348 --> 08:37.933
People thinking
their partner will change?

08:38.059 --> 08:40.477
That's another reason marriages fail.

08:44.107 --> 08:48.235
People don't change, at least
not in any way that really matters.

08:54.659 --> 08:56.994
I think you've had enough caffeine.

08:57.120 --> 09:00.331
You were right.
It's not his throat, it's his lungs.

09:00.457 --> 09:02.583
The plethysmograph revealed
decreased lung capacity.

09:02.709 --> 09:04.293
And the CT showed lung
scarring.

09:04.419 --> 09:07.296
It's definitely interstitial
pulmonary fibrosis.

09:07.422 --> 09:11.383
What's not definite is the cause.
There's no arthritis, no sarcoidosis.

09:11.509 --> 09:14.678
He's not on any prescription meds.
And he's a wedding photographer.

09:14.804 --> 09:17.223
So I doubt he got exposed to coal dust
or asbestos at work.

09:17.349 --> 09:20.226
- Cause could be idiopathic.
- Can't be idiopathic.

09:20.352 --> 09:22.144
Idiopathic means without a known cause.

09:22.270 --> 09:23.312
What I meant was that...

09:23.438 --> 09:25.606
What you meant was
you don't know what the cause is.

09:25.732 --> 09:28.317
Just say that and we can avoid
this conversation.

09:29.694 --> 09:31.070
No applause?

09:32.656 --> 09:34.782
- What's his current condition?
- Stable.

09:34.908 --> 09:36.575
- Well, then we can wait.
- Wait for what?

09:36.701 --> 09:39.370
For whatever you can't figure out
to cause something else.

09:39.496 --> 09:40.621
You know it's going to.

09:40.747 --> 09:42.915
It's possible the IPF
could just continue to...

09:50.715 --> 09:52.925
- There's something wrong with his skin.
- Do something.

09:53.051 --> 09:56.178
- Stop scratching. Let me look at it.
- I can't. This is driving me crazy.

09:56.304 --> 09:58.347
Stop scratching, so we can...
Make it stop!

09:58.473 --> 10:00.724
- OK...
- Make it stop!

10:00.850 --> 10:02.518
Make it stop!

10:11.528 --> 10:13.237
Now we've got
something to discuss.

10:13.363 --> 10:17.533
What causes both lung scarring
and the itchy, splotchy red blotchies?

10:17.659 --> 10:20.160
It's obviously not a reaction
to medication.

10:20.287 --> 10:21.870
We haven't given him any yet.

10:21.997 --> 10:24.123
Right. But what besides
what it's obviously not,

10:24.249 --> 10:26.125
can cause both lung scarring
and the splotches?

10:26.251 --> 10:27.376
Where are you going?

10:27.502 --> 10:30.629
To complete the second half
of the caffeine delivery system.

10:32.882 --> 10:34.550
Either talk louder, or get in here.

10:42.684 --> 10:46.270
Same color coming out as going in.
Do you think that's a marketing thing?

10:46.396 --> 10:48.314
A lupus could cause lung scarring
and a rash.

10:48.440 --> 10:50.733
Or could still be a food allergy.

10:50.859 --> 10:53.444
- We've already ruled out allergies.
- Did we?

10:53.570 --> 10:54.611
Where's Cameron?

10:54.738 --> 10:56.322
We're in the men's room.

10:56.448 --> 10:59.241
We need an allergy expert in here.

11:03.830 --> 11:06.707
- This can wait two minutes.
- You don't know that.

11:06.833 --> 11:09.501
Chase thinks that food allergy
should still be on the table.

11:09.627 --> 11:11.670
No, it wouldn't explain
the lung scarring.

11:11.796 --> 11:13.714
Some homeopathic studies
have found a connection

11:13.840 --> 11:15.883
between food allergies
and autoimmune reactions,

11:16.009 --> 11:17.551
which could cause lung inflammation.

11:17.677 --> 11:19.803
Yeah. And some homeopathic studies
have also found

11:19.929 --> 11:22.639
that ground-up spiders can cure cancer.
Can I go now?

11:22.766 --> 11:23.932
No.

11:24.726 --> 11:28.854
Lungs, skin, skin, lungs.

11:28.980 --> 11:30.981
Sklungs?

11:32.776 --> 11:34.443
Lungs, skin...

11:36.279 --> 11:37.863
...throat.

11:41.201 --> 11:43.494
Heavy metal toxicity.

11:43.620 --> 11:46.121
It explains the lungs, the itching,

11:46.247 --> 11:48.957
the swelling in his tongue and throat.

11:49.084 --> 11:52.336
I thought you didn't believe there was
anything wrong with his throat.

11:52.462 --> 11:56.131
I never said I didn't believe it. I just
said I had good reason to doubt it.

11:56.257 --> 11:57.466
And now?

11:57.592 --> 11:59.134
I have good reason
to doubt those doubts.

11:59.260 --> 12:01.970
The patient's a little old
to be chewing paint off the walls.

12:02.097 --> 12:04.181
Nor does he drink well water,
eat fish every day,

12:04.307 --> 12:07.059
or do anything else that could have
exposed him to heavy metals.

12:07.185 --> 12:10.062
He and his wife worked a wedding
at Cabo San Lucas last month.

12:10.188 --> 12:12.898
A lot of pottery in Mexico
is contaminated with lead-based paint.

12:13.024 --> 12:15.734
Now aren't you glad you joined us?

12:15.860 --> 12:19.113
Search their house, screen his blood
and hair for lead.

12:19.614 --> 12:22.032
Test for mercury and arsenic
while you're at it.

12:22.158 --> 12:25.035
And, Chase, find out
what the resort cooks with,

12:25.161 --> 12:27.496
if they repainted recently
or did any plumbing repairs.

12:28.706 --> 12:31.667
- But I don't speak Spanish.
- Then it'll be challenging.

12:43.513 --> 12:46.390
Good Lord, what is that smell?

12:47.350 --> 12:49.059
Stuffed pepper.

12:50.228 --> 12:52.980
Stuffed with what? Vomit?

13:03.324 --> 13:05.200
I thought you were going to a hotel.

13:05.326 --> 13:07.911
I found an apartment.
I can move in on Monday.

13:08.037 --> 13:10.372
- Is that fast enough for you?
- What's today?

13:12.417 --> 13:16.170
- Where'd you get all that stuff?
- Not from your kitchen.

13:16.296 --> 13:21.008
Don't you ever eat anything
besides canned soup and peanut butter?

13:21.134 --> 13:23.051
Don't you ever eat anything
that doesn't look like

13:23.178 --> 13:25.804
it's been rolled onto your plate
by a dung beetle?

13:28.808 --> 13:30.476
Try it.

13:35.940 --> 13:38.442
- It's good, isn't it?
- No.

13:39.444 --> 13:41.361
Just better than it looks.

13:43.990 --> 13:46.283
How much beans and rice
do you think you'd have to eat

13:46.409 --> 13:48.994
from a ceramic pot
painted with lead-based paint

13:49.120 --> 13:51.455
to get enough lead into your system
to damage your lungs?

13:51.581 --> 13:54.249
- Are we talking a child, or an adult?
- Adult.

13:54.375 --> 13:55.501
Then I would say a lot.

13:55.627 --> 13:58.378
You'd have to eat beans
every day for months.

13:59.422 --> 14:03.217
Now, why do you have a season pass
to the New Yankee workshop?

14:03.343 --> 14:06.053
It's a complete moron
working with power tools.

14:06.179 --> 14:08.388
How much more suspenseful
can you get?

14:08.515 --> 14:10.599
I'm... I was watching something.

14:10.725 --> 14:12.559
No, you were about to watch something.

14:12.685 --> 14:15.479
I'm watching something.
See the difference?

14:17.524 --> 14:19.858
If the water was contaminated,
wouldn't I be sick, too?

14:19.984 --> 14:23.028
People can metabolize toxins
at different rates.

14:23.154 --> 14:25.030
We'll test it to be sure.

14:25.573 --> 14:28.534
- Have you done any recent renovations?
- No.

14:29.661 --> 14:31.995
Have any problem with bugs or rodents?

14:32.121 --> 14:33.413
Just the occasional ant.

14:35.458 --> 14:36.708
Use bug spray?

14:36.834 --> 14:38.627
No, I hate the smell.

14:39.087 --> 14:42.631
Luckily both of us are pretty anal
about keeping things clean.

14:43.424 --> 14:44.675
Yeah, I can tell.

14:57.105 --> 14:58.564
You think ants are the problem?

14:58.690 --> 15:01.191
Can you stop stuffing your mouth
with pancakes for one second?

15:01.317 --> 15:04.319
These aren't pancakes.
These are macadamia nut pancakes.

15:04.445 --> 15:06.321
Wilson made them and they're amazing.

15:06.447 --> 15:08.407
She says she doesn't use bug spray.

15:08.533 --> 15:10.784
Like little silver dollar
slices of heaven.

15:10.910 --> 15:14.037
- Some ants are poisonous, maybe...
- Forget the 72 virgins.

15:14.163 --> 15:16.331
If I blow myself up
in a crowded restaurant,

15:16.457 --> 15:19.251
I'm going to be asking
for a plate of these babies.

15:19.377 --> 15:21.587
Was the ant big and red
or small and black?

15:21.713 --> 15:25.257
- Medium and brown.
- Halle Berry brown or Beyoncé brown?

15:25.383 --> 15:29.720
Is there a difference?

15:30.471 --> 15:34.975
Army ants could devour, dissolve
and eat a cow in a matter of hours.

15:35.101 --> 15:38.186
Australian Bull ants, on the other hand,

15:38.313 --> 15:41.398
nasty little bastards,
but more of a nuisance than a threat.

15:41.524 --> 15:44.067
- No surprise there.
- Beyoncé.

15:44.736 --> 15:46.570
Well, then that's not it.

15:46.696 --> 15:48.864
How much clay did he eat at the resort?

15:48.990 --> 15:52.242
It's a five-star, $400 a night place.
They don't cook with ceramic pots.

15:52.368 --> 15:53.493
Tox screen?

15:53.620 --> 15:55.579
No evidence of lead, mercury or arsenic.

15:55.705 --> 15:59.583
Run them again. Call the resort, find
some disgruntled employee to talk to.

15:59.709 --> 16:01.501
- Go back to the home...
- It's not heavy metals.

16:01.628 --> 16:03.795
- The symptoms say it is.
- The tests say it's not.

16:03.921 --> 16:05.964
Who you going to believe?
The symptoms or the test?

16:06.090 --> 16:09.176
- It could also be a food allergy.
- Cameron says it's not.

16:09.302 --> 16:11.345
If your test could be wrong,
why can't hers?

16:11.471 --> 16:14.640
His diet hasn't changed since he was
a kid. His favorite food is cornflakes.

16:14.766 --> 16:16.808
Which, I assume, he eats with milk,

16:16.934 --> 16:18.935
one of the most common
adult onset food allergies.

16:19.062 --> 16:22.314
Start treating him for lead poisoning.
It's the most likely heavy metal.

16:22.440 --> 16:25.734
And, yeah, you can test him for
allergies for dairy, wheat and legume.

16:32.784 --> 16:35.827
I am not having an affair
with my daughter's karate instructor

16:35.953 --> 16:39.956
- and I did not give my husband herpes.
- Find out where House is.

16:44.420 --> 16:45.837
If you're convinced it's allergies,

16:45.963 --> 16:48.090
why are you giving him drugs
to treat lead poisoning?

16:48.216 --> 16:49.633
We're not convinced of anything yet.

16:49.759 --> 16:52.052
I think I need something else,
this cream isn't working.

16:52.178 --> 16:53.720
We're doing everything we can.

16:55.181 --> 16:57.432
Sorry.

16:57.558 --> 16:59.309
No, no. It's not my back, it's my feet!

16:59.435 --> 17:02.104
I think I stepped in something
when I went to the bathroom.

17:02.230 --> 17:03.939
Oh, it's on my socks. It's burning.

17:07.485 --> 17:08.860
I don't see anything.

17:08.986 --> 17:12.406
Please, take my socks off!
Wait, wait, wait, wait, wait.

17:13.616 --> 17:17.494
- Ow! Stop! Stop! Stop!
- What did you just scratch him with?

17:17.620 --> 17:21.456
If there was an allergic reaction, it
would be on his back, not on his feet.

17:21.582 --> 17:23.333
Oh, it's burning,
please make it stop!

17:23.459 --> 17:25.794
We need some gabapentin in here.

17:29.298 --> 17:32.384
Excruciating pain
in the lower extremities.

17:32.510 --> 17:35.971
- Not a sign of a food allergy.
- Means there's a neurological problem.

17:36.097 --> 17:40.058
More significantly, it's yet another
classic sign of heavy metals.

17:40.184 --> 17:43.186
And I just did yet another
hair and blood test for lead,

17:43.312 --> 17:45.605
and everything else he could
have possibly been exposed to.

17:45.732 --> 17:47.858
They're all negative.
It's gotta be something else.

17:47.984 --> 17:49.317
- Lupus could cause...
- No.

17:49.444 --> 17:51.987
Lupus progresses slower.
There'd be joint pain.

17:52.113 --> 17:54.239
So it's not a typical case.

17:54.365 --> 17:56.992
- We should get an ANA.
- It's not lupus.

17:58.035 --> 17:59.578
The symptoms don't match.

17:59.704 --> 18:01.747
And the tests don't match heavy metals.

18:11.299 --> 18:13.842
It's happening again.
He's not breathing.

18:16.471 --> 18:19.264
Tongue swelling, airway's closing.
He's not getting any air.

18:19.390 --> 18:21.516
- His lungs are clear.
- We're gonna have to intubate.

18:21.642 --> 18:23.894
Try to relax, Bob.
This is gonna help you breathe.

18:24.020 --> 18:25.270
Oh, my God!

18:25.396 --> 18:27.063
He's gonna aspirate! Need suction!

18:27.190 --> 18:29.441
- What's happening?
- Suction.

18:29.567 --> 18:32.110
There's too much vomit. We're never
going to be able to intubate.

18:32.236 --> 18:35.363
- We're gonna have to trach him.
- He's not breathing!

18:59.138 --> 19:01.932
His urine has elevated
proteins and red blood cells.

19:02.058 --> 19:04.684
It's lupus-induced kidney failure.
If we don't start treatment...

19:04.811 --> 19:06.812
Heavy metal toxicity
could cause vomiting.

19:06.938 --> 19:09.523
So would lupus nephritis,
and it also causes tissue swelling.

