37:51.728 --> 37:55.481
You didn't want me to go to the
bathroom because you wanted to tell me

37:55.607 --> 37:59.777
my husband is going to be fine
and that you used to live in Egypt?

37:59.903 --> 38:02.821
I didn't have a problem
with you going to the bathroom.

38:02.948 --> 38:05.866
I just didn't want you
to wash your hands.

38:08.370 --> 38:10.496
I never actually found a mummy,

38:10.622 --> 38:13.707
but I did learn a fair amount
about the ancient Egyptians.

38:13.833 --> 38:16.460
For example, they discovered
that stannous chloride

38:16.586 --> 38:20.506
is not only great for toughening
ruby glass, but if it's mixed with gold,

38:20.632 --> 38:22.633
it turns bright purple.

38:29.724 --> 38:33.769
Now, either your fingers actually
are worth their weight in gold...

38:34.980 --> 38:37.398
...or you've been sprinkling
your husband's cereal

38:37.524 --> 38:39.733
with gold sodium thiomalate.

38:39.859 --> 38:42.528
It's an arthritis remedy.
It's rarely used here in the U.S.,

38:42.654 --> 38:46.699
but it's still popular in Mexico.
Gotta give you props.

38:48.743 --> 38:51.203
Never heard of anyone using gold before.

38:52.831 --> 38:56.375
It's almost poetic.

38:58.962 --> 39:00.254
That's ridiculous.

39:00.380 --> 39:03.507
Heavy metal tox screen for gold
was off the chart.

39:07.303 --> 39:10.180
- Why would I...
- Because you were trying to kill him.

39:11.016 --> 39:14.059
I'd love to know the why
behind that why.

39:15.020 --> 39:17.563
But you're not gonna tell me, are you?

39:18.940 --> 39:20.524
You're wrong.

39:22.861 --> 39:24.236
I love Bob.

39:25.864 --> 39:27.906
I never said you didn't love him.

39:33.621 --> 39:37.624
How could somebody do that?
Sit by someone's bedside day and night

39:37.751 --> 39:41.003
helping them, comforting them
and at the same time killing them?

39:41.129 --> 39:43.047
Maybe he was having an affair.

39:43.173 --> 39:44.965
Maybe she was having an affair.

39:45.091 --> 39:48.594
Or maybe she just gets her kicks out
of slowly sucking the life out of a guy,

39:48.720 --> 39:51.513
- watching him suffer.
- He must have done something to her.

39:51.639 --> 39:53.974
- Yeah, he had it coming.
- I didn't say he deserved it.

39:54.100 --> 39:56.727
The only thing he did wrong
was marry a sociopath.

39:56.853 --> 39:59.605
Or maybe she just got tired
of being married.

40:00.857 --> 40:02.858
Didn't want to admit
to family and friends

40:02.984 --> 40:06.070
that the marriage
everyone thought was perfect, wasn't.

40:06.196 --> 40:09.448
Shouldn't one of us stay with her?
What if she tries to run?

40:09.574 --> 40:11.575
Yeah, Cameron, go back there.

40:12.202 --> 40:15.037
It'd be weird if we were
all in the ladies' room.

40:44.609 --> 40:47.611
We started chelation therapy
with dimercaprol.

40:49.864 --> 40:51.573
Thrilled to hear it.

40:52.700 --> 40:54.701
His kidney function hasn't improved.

40:54.828 --> 40:56.620
It will.

40:56.746 --> 40:58.956
He's gonna need a lung transplant.

41:00.917 --> 41:03.961
He's becoming more attractive
by the minute, isn't he?

41:05.797 --> 41:07.381
You're pleased.

41:07.507 --> 41:11.468
You think you've proved
that every marriage is a mistake.

41:11.594 --> 41:13.387
Do I look pleased?

41:34.576 --> 41:36.368
Ignorance is bliss.

42:36.721 --> 42:39.181
You have one new message.

42:39.766 --> 42:42.434
Hi, this is Blake Hanson
calling for Dr. Wilson.

42:42.560 --> 42:44.478
I got a better offer for the apartment.

42:44.604 --> 42:46.188
I know I offered it to you already,

42:46.314 --> 42:48.357
so if you match the offer
you can still have the place.

42:48.483 --> 42:51.068
Make sure you call me first thing
in the morning and let me know.

42:51.194 --> 42:53.528
Otherwise, well, you've got my number.

43:03.539 --> 43:05.707
Message deleted.
